# 💉 COMMAND: load
Description: Dynamically loads a Python exploit, module, or compiled ELF binary directly into the memory of an active C2 session. 

Python modules are converted into pure-Python fileless loaders. Compiled binaries (.elf, .bin) are automatically wrapped in a `memfd_create` payload to execute directly from RAM without touching the target's hard drive.

Usage (Inside an active session):
    load <path_to_exploit_or_binary>

Examples:
    Session 1> load /Users/donald/.SuperSploit/exploits/linux/cve_2022_0847_dirtypipe.py
    Session 1> load /Users/donald/Downloads/cve-2024-1086.elf

Requirements:
    - You must be interacting with an active C2 session (`sessions -i <ID>`).
    - Python modules must support the `silent=True` argument and return a loader string.

Note: The loaded module or binary is registered as a background function in the target's memory. The console will instruct you on the exact function name to call (e.g., `dirtypipe()` or `run_cve_2024_1086_elf()`) to trigger execution.